/iTrade/indicators/README
===============================================================================

This file contains information for all official indicators distributed with
iTrade

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What is an indicator ?
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

An indicator is a .py file that appears in iTrade's indicators folder. iTrade
tries to import all such files while starting up. During the importation, each
indicator register to the system.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
How do indicators work ?
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Indicators register themselves when iTrade imports them using specific code,
which should appear as the outer level of the .py file.

<under construction>

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Indicators Management
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

iTrade loads indicators in the order they appear in the file
./indicators/indicators.txt

The first mention of an indicator in this file controls whether the indicator
is enabled or not:
   - if the indicator's name is commented out, it is disabled, otherwise it is
     enabled
   - Indicators not appearing in this file are disabled.

File names may be indented as desired

